{"id":229,"date":"2019-11-27T14:32:20","date_gmt":"2019-11-27T13:32:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.gotriple.eu\/?p=229"},"modified":"2020-04-29T11:00:28","modified_gmt":"2020-04-29T09:00:28","slug":"triple-kick-off-meeting","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/2019\/11\/triple-kick-off-meeting\/","title":{"rendered":"TRIPLE Kick-Off Meeting"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"modal-ready\"><p>\n<!--StartFragment--><\/p>\n\n\n<p>The Kick-Off of the TRIPLE project, funded in the Horizon 2020 framework, takes place on the <strong>4<sup>th<\/sup> <\/strong><strong>of December 2019<\/strong>, at the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.mshparisnord.fr\/\" target=\"_blank\">Maison des Sciences de l\u2019homme<\/a> Paris-Nord (20 Avenue George Sand, 93210 Saint-Denis) from <strong>2 to 6 pm<\/strong>. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The event, which is  hosted by OPERAS and Huma-Num, will be opened by an  introduction of David Fiala from the French Ministry of Higher  Education and Research (<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.enseignementsup-recherche.gouv.fr\/\" target=\"_blank\">MESRI<\/a>), Lionel Maurel, Scientific Deputy Director (<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http:\/\/www.cnrs.fr\/\" target=\"_blank\">CNRS<\/a>, <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/inshs.cnrs.fr\/\" target=\"_blank\">INSHS<\/a>), and a <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.huma-num.fr\/\" target=\"_blank\">Huma-Num<\/a>  representative. Afterwards, Suzanne Dumouchel, Coordinator of TRIPLE  and Co-Coordinator of OPERAS will present TRIPLE with its goals and  challenges. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>After a coffee break, Pierre Mounier, Deputy Director, Head of the International Department (<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.openedition.org\/\" target=\"_blank\">OpenEdition<\/a>)  and Co-Coordinator of OPERAS, will present TRIPLE as a Core Service of  the European Research Infrastructure OPERAS. Ivana Ilija\u0161i\u0107 Ver\u0161i\u0107,  Chief Operations Officer (<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.cessda.eu\/\" target=\"_blank\">CESSDA<\/a>), will discuss the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/sshopencloud.eu\/\" target=\"_blank\">SSHOC<\/a> project to present TRIPLE in a broader ecosystem. Elena Giglia, Head of the Open Access Office at the University of Turin (<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"http:\/\/www.unito.it\/\" target=\"_blank\">UniTo<\/a>), will introduce the <a href=\"https:\/\/operas.hypotheses.org\/2732\">CO-OPERAS<\/a> Implementation Network and the connection with TRIPLE.&nbsp;Afterwards, there will be a cocktail buffet (6 to 8 pm). <\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p>Everyone is warmly welcome. Persons and institutions whose work focuses  on open science and research data in Europe, including representatives  of academic publishers, repositories, journal editorial boards, and  research institutions are particularly encouraged to attend. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Kindly confirm your attendance via e-mail to Emilie Bloti\u00e8re  (emilie.blotiere[at]huma-num.fr) and Suzanne Dumouchel  (suzanne.dumouchel[at]huma-num.fr). <\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n<p><!--EndFragment--><\/p><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Kick-Off of the TRIPLE project, funded in the Horizon 2020 framework, takes place on the 4th of December 2019, at the Maison des Sciences de l\u2019homme Paris-Nord (20 Avenue George Sand, 93210 Saint-Denis) from 2 to 6 pm. The<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":189,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[4],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/229"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=229"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/229\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":231,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/229\/revisions\/231"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/189"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=229"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=229"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=229"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}